\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Sausage, Kale, and Lentil Soup\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4 servings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs36 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/olive-oil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 extra-virgin olive oil}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound hot sausage, bulk or casing removed\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 onion, chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 ribs celery, chopped, leafy tops reserved\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 large carrot, peeled and chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 large Idaho (russet) potato, peeled and chopped into small dice\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 Fresno or Holland {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chile/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chile pepper}}, thinly sliced or finely chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 sprigs fresh rosemary, leaves picked and finely chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cloves garlic}}, chopped or sliced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 tablespoon ground cumin\
{\listtext	\'95	}Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 bundle Tuscan, black, or dinosaur kale, stemmed and very thinly sliced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup tomato paste\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup white wine\
{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly grated nutmeg\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 3/4 cups lentils\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stock/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chicken stock}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups water\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 In a soup pot or large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dutch-oven/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Dutch oven}}, heat 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. Add the sausage, breaking it into pieces, and cook until lightly brown. Add the onions, celery, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/carrot/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 carrots}}, potato, chile pepper, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rosemary/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 rosemary}}, garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper, and cook to soften, 8 to10 minutes.\
Wilt in the kale, and season the kale leaves with a little freshly grated nutmeg. Stir in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato-paste/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tomato paste}} for 30 seconds, then add white wine. Cook to reduce by 1/2 and stir in the lentils, stock, and water. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to low, and simmer the soup until the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lentil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lentils}} are tender, about 35 minutes. Serve immediately or cool, store, and reheat. Serve with chopped celery greens, to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garnish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garnish}}\
}